when Leah was here.

34:54.393 --> 34:57.229
But then you asked me if I was
wearing a sweatshirt like you

34:57.263 --> 35:00.766
were when--
- I made a mistake.

35:00.799 --> 35:03.169
- That's a pretty big mistake,
Laurel.

35:03.202 --> 35:08.840
You said that you spattered
paint on Leah's sweatshirt.

35:08.874 --> 35:11.510
Tell me about
that night again, the night

35:11.543 --> 35:14.313
when your mother took Leah
to the dance recital

35:14.346 --> 35:16.915
and you were home alone
with your father.

35:16.948 --> 35:22.421
- I already told you.
- So tell me again.

35:22.454 --> 35:25.791
- We had hot dogs.

35:25.824 --> 35:27.659
Daddy couldn't cook
to save his life

35:27.693 --> 35:29.661
so we ordered from the deli.

35:29.695 --> 35:31.430
- You said you played cards.

35:31.463 --> 35:33.465
- After we ate.

35:35.301 --> 35:37.903
- So when you
finished playing cards,

35:37.936 --> 35:39.405
what did you do?

35:39.438 --> 35:43.209
- I already told you.
- Tell me again.

35:43.242 --> 35:44.710
I got ready for bed.

35:44.743 --> 35:46.845
- And you put your nightie on.

35:46.878 --> 35:50.749
- It was pink
with white flowers.

35:50.782 --> 35:53.185
And I got into bed.

35:53.219 --> 35:55.954
And I waited for him
to tuck me in

35:55.987 --> 35:58.590
'cause that's
what he always did.

35:58.624 --> 36:03.229
Only this time he got
into bed with me.

36:03.262 --> 36:07.299
And we kissed.

36:07.333 --> 36:11.503
Not the way we normally kissed.
We kissed like grown-ups.

36:15.674 --> 36:17.943
- Like...

36:17.976 --> 36:20.746
Like lovers.
- Mm-hmm.

36:20.779 --> 36:22.448
- And then what?

36:22.481 --> 36:27.253
- And then he was
under the covers.

36:27.286 --> 36:30.589
When he took his pants off
so I didn't see it.

36:30.622 --> 36:33.592
And he said the pain
would go away.

36:33.625 --> 36:36.628
- Did it?

36:36.662 --> 36:38.330
- It was beautiful.

36:38.364 --> 36:43.702
- Were you scared?
- A little.

36:43.735 --> 36:45.337
- Just a little?

36:45.371 --> 36:48.374
- I wanted him to be happy.

36:51.410 --> 36:53.945
- Did you know it was wrong?

36:53.979 --> 36:56.782
- He did it with Leah.

36:56.815 --> 36:59.685
- You were six years old,
Laurel.

36:59.718 --> 37:02.354
The pain.

37:02.388 --> 37:07.459
How could anything
that hurt so much

37:07.493 --> 37:11.897
not feel wrong?

37:11.930 --> 37:14.566
- We made love.
- No, you did not.

37:14.600 --> 37:16.735
- We made love.
- No, you didn't.

37:16.768 --> 37:19.838
[softly] Stop.

37:19.871 --> 37:24.910
You got to stop.

37:24.943 --> 37:28.280
Laurel.

37:28.314 --> 37:32.518
I've been doing
this a long time.

37:32.551 --> 37:37.956
Women who are raped
and children who are abused

37:37.989 --> 37:42.761
don't say "we did this,
and we did that."

37:42.794 --> 37:46.532
They talk about what
their attacker did to them

37:46.565 --> 37:49.568
just like you did when you
told me about Greg Harvey.

37:49.601 --> 37:52.671
You said that he pushed
you onto the bed,

37:52.704 --> 37:55.607
that he shoved his tongue
into your mouth.

37:55.641 --> 37:57.909
- [exhales deeply]

37:57.943 --> 38:00.779
- Laurel.

38:00.812 --> 38:04.316
Is it possible...

38:04.350 --> 38:07.519
maybe that this is
in your head?

38:07.553 --> 38:10.088
That this is...
- No.

38:10.121 --> 38:12.524
- A fantasy?
- No.

38:12.558 --> 38:14.826
- And that it never happened?

38:14.860 --> 38:16.428
- No.

38:16.462 --> 38:19.731
- That all those times
at your beach house

38:19.765 --> 38:24.403
when you were unbuttoning
one more button on your blouse

38:24.436 --> 38:28.907
or walking around in your
panties in front of your father

38:28.940 --> 38:32.077
when he was watching TV...

38:32.110 --> 38:34.813
That was Leah.
Not you.

38:34.846 --> 38:36.848
- He loved me.

38:36.882 --> 38:39.418
- Not like he loved Leah.

38:39.451 --> 38:41.420
[whispering] You were jealous.

38:41.453 --> 38:44.590
Jealous of your sister.

38:44.623 --> 38:46.925
- I was just as pretty
and just as smart.

38:46.958 --> 38:48.827
- I'm sure that you were.

38:48.860 --> 38:51.129
But your father never noticed.

38:51.162 --> 38:54.366
*

38:54.400 --> 38:57.603
So he turned you
into that sad girl.

38:57.636 --> 39:04.075
And wondering
why he never chooses you.

39:04.109 --> 39:08.880
But Leah was the antelope

39:08.914 --> 39:12.684
that was caught by the cheetah.

39:12.718 --> 39:19.057
And you were just one
of the herd passing by.

39:19.090 --> 39:24.095
All those years
and he never picked you.

39:24.129 --> 39:26.498
- He loved me.

39:26.532 --> 39:29.167
He said I was beautiful--
- Like Greg Harvey

39:29.200 --> 39:31.036
